snippet.textDisplay: Well here are few memories...I am from a band which was called SILK ROUTE...JUNOON and us travelled quite a lot i India together...remember Dooba Dooba and Boondein...well needless to say there was great joy/masti/sharing/jamming/love and respect for each other..and those still remain tho both the bands not really there...but the music is immortal and infinite and still lives on forever...and after all these years its awesome to see Salmanbhai rock his axe and still remains as fresh and Ali Noor and me together  with his brother jammed a lot in India and played together for a PARIKRAMA and Friends Concert cos that was my other band I was part of....AWESOME ARRANGEMENTS AND UIRAR SOLOS..being a guitar player...lil biased...lol.Coke Studio Pakistan...u guys are rocking and red hot..Lotsa Love and God bless.

snippet.textDisplay: Just one thing that comes to my mind  .. wow !. Took me back to sometime in the 90s . A taxi driver in Mumbai who was taking me to the airport had Junoon's Azadi cassette in his cab's stereo and soon both of us were grooving to Sayonee. Impressed ,  I asked him which band it was and his reply was "pata nahi saab , Pakistan ka koi hai" . I noted the album title and was able to locate the CD in Oman which I brought back and still have  to this day. The original guitar solo of Sayonee was the first solo I tried to learn when I bought my first electric guitar .. ( still cant do it perfectly unfortunately : - (  )   That guitar solo in the second half by Salman Ahmed was  very tastefully done ..
